 ($M_{\\|}$), showing instead a sharp decrease beyond $\\sim\n\\mu_0 H_{\\|} = $ 4 T which is the field required to align the magnetic moments\nalong $\\mu_0 H_{\\|}$. We argue that locally chiral spin structures, such as\nskyrmions, and possibly skyrmion tubes, lead to a field dependent\nspin-chirality and hence to a novel type of topological anomalous transport.\nLocally chiral spin-structures are captured by our Monte-Carlo simulations\nincorporating small Dzyaloshinskii-Moriya and biquadratic exchange\ninteractions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jun 2021 01:29:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Oct 2021 19:47:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-15"}
